      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEKTRA DAMIAN (3) is a capable type and proved too strong last time to win by 5 lengths at this track in a handy 22.34 beating Cruising Nat. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. DIVA'S ROSE (6) was big odds last time but gave a huge sight after a fast early split, grabbed late but holding on to a placing when a 2.5 lengths second (22.51) over 390m at this track. Must be included in calculations. BUSH BUDDY (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (23.27) last time in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 at Geelong. Has a good record at this journey. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Deserves plenty of respect. PAW HAZELDON (2) is hard to fault of late and is a strong top-three hope again.",
